From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 11:54:16 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix(loop): add read-path staleness gate + real statusline
 self-heal (#2625)

The statusline file is regenerated only by a tick's render_phase, and both
readers (hooks/scripts/statusline.sh and `t3 loop status`) display it verbatim,
so a dead or long-not-ticked loop renders a confident, frozen loop line with no
warning. Three fixes:

- Freshness banner on the read path. The tick now records `rendered_at` in
  tick-meta.json; both readers compute now - rendered_at (falling back to the
  meta file's mtime) and, past max(2*cadence, 300s), prepend a RED
  stale-statusline line naming how long ago the last tick ran. The cutoff and
  wording live in one place, teatree.loop.statusline_staleness, so the shell
  hook and the CLI agree; the hook mirrors the arithmetic inline to stay a
  fast, dependency-free read. Degrades silently on missing/broken meta.

- Real detector self-heal. StaleStatuslineEntryDetector's auto_fix was a no-op
  stub. Add the idle render seam teatree.loop.phases.render.rerender_statusline
  (orchestration layer) and inject it as the action-ladder auto_fix_callable
  from the tick piggyback, so a merged-PR / terminal-ticket URL actually drops
  out of the file. The detector stays in the domain layer and never reaches up
  (tach-enforced); the schedule's _detector_auto_fix routes each detector's own
  rerender. Whole-render age (a dead loop) is covered by the read-path banner,
  not the detector, since the detector cannot fire when the loop is not ticking.

Anti-vacuous regression tests, each observed RED before the fix: shell-hook
banner (stale shows it with the right minutes, fresh hides it, missing meta is
silent), CLI status banner (same age-gating), the shared staleness_banner helper
across the cutoff boundary, the rerender_statusline seam rewriting a stale file,
and the schedule adapter routing the detector's own rerender. Docs updated:
BLUEPRINT and loop-topology.md.
